{"type":"message","id":"e26cdf9d","parentId":"ec996740","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:43:27.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n1. Audit reports saved locally only, no push to messaging channels\n2. Git backup needs to be configured\n\nLet me proceed with:\n- Step 3: Write the nightly audit script and register cron job (local reports only, no announce)\n- Step 4: Help configure git backup\n\nLet me start writing the audit script. This is a big script with 13 check items. Let me also create the necessary directories.\n\nFirst, let me check what skills/MCPs are installed so I know what to baseline.\n\nLet me also create the known issues exclusion JSON file.\n\nFor the cron job, since there's no messaging channel, I'll set it up to just run the script and save reports locally. The cron will still use an isolated session to execute.\n\nActually wait - the guide says to use `openclaw cron add` with `--announce` and `--to`. But since there's no channel configured, I should skip the announce part. The reports will be saved to `$OC/security-reports/`.\n\nLet me write the script first, then register the cron, then do Step 4 (git).\n\nLet me write a comprehensive audit script covering all 13 items.\n\nFor the script, I need to:\n1. Use `set -uo pipefail`\n2. Print section headers with `=== [N] Name ===`\n3. Handle empty output with explicit OK messages\n4. Generate summary at the end\n5. Save report to $OC/security-reports/\n6. Support known issues exclusion from JSON\n7. Rotate reports older than 30 days\n\nLet me write this carefully.\n\nFor item 13 (git backup), since we're about to set up git, I should include it in the script but handle gracefully if not configured yet.\n\nLet me also need to create:\n- `$HOME/.openclaw/security-reports/` directory\n- `$HOME/.openclaw/.security-audit-known-issues.json` empty array\n- The script itself at `$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/nightly-security-audit.sh`\n\nLet me write the script now. I'll need to be thorough but also keep it manageable.\n\nActually, let me think about what commands need sudo. The script might need sudo for:\n- `ss -tnp` / `ss -unp` (to see process names for all connections)\n- Reading `/proc/<pid>/environ` for gateway\n- `chattr` checks\n- `journalctl` (might work without sudo)\n- `lastlog`\n\nFor the cron, since it runs in an isolated session, it will also need exec approval... hmm. Let me think about this.\n\nActually the cron job runs the script via an isolated agent session. The agent in that session would need to execute the bash script. But exec approval might block it. This is a problem.\n\nLet me focus on writing the script and registering the cron first. We can work out the approval flow later.\n\nLet me write the script now.\n\nFor the known issues JSON, I need to create it as an empty array initially.\n\nLet me write everything:\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# nightly-security-audit.sh - OpenClaw Nightly Security Audit\n# Part of: OpenClaw 极简安全实践指南 v2.8\n# Generated: 2026-04-02 by 樱桃 (Cherry) 🍒\n\nset -uo pipefail\n\nOC=\"${OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR:-$HOME/.openclaw}\"\nREPORT_DIR=\"$OC/security-reports\"\nKNOWN_ISSUES=\"$OC/.security-audit-known-issues.json\"\nDATE=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')\nREPORT_FILE=\"$REPORT_DIR/audit-$DATE.txt\"\nTODAY_MEMORY=\"$OC/workspace/memory/$(date '+%Y-%m-%d').md\"\n\n# Counters\nCRITICAL=0\nWARN=0\nOK=0\n\nmkdir -p \"$REPORT_DIR\"\n\n# Helper: increment counters\ncount_critical() { ((CRITICAL++)) || true; }\ncount_warn() { ((WARN++)) || true; }\ncount_ok() { ((OK++)) || true; }\n\n# Helper: apply known issues exclusion\n# Reads the JSON file and marks matching lines\napply_exclusions() {\n    local check_name=\"$1\"\n    local input=\"$2\"\n    \n    if [[ ! -f \"$KNOWN_ISSUES\" ]] || [[ ! -s \"$KNOWN_ISSUES\" ]]; then\n        echo \"$input\"\n        return\n    fi\n    \n    # Extract patterns for this check\n    local patterns\n    patterns=$(python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\ntry:\n    with open('$KNOWN_ISSUES') as f:\n        issues = json.load(f)\n    for item in issues:\n        if item.get('check') == '$check_name':\n            print(item.get('pattern', '') + '|||' + item.get('reason', 'known issue'))\nexcept:\n    pass\n\" 2>/dev/null)\n    \n    if [[ -z \"$patterns\" ]]; then\n        echo \"$input\"\n        return\n    fi\n    \n    local result=\"$input\"\n    while IFS='|||' read -r pattern reason; do\n        [[ -z \"$pattern\" ]] && continue\n        result=$(echo \"$result\" | sed \"s|.*${pattern}.*|[已知问题-忽略: ${reason}] &|\")\n    done <<< \"$patterns\"\n    echo \"$result\"\n}\n\nexec > >(tee \"$REPORT_FILE\") 2>&1\n\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"  OpenClaw Nightly Security Audit\"\necho \"  Date: $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')\"\necho \"  Host: $(hostname)\"\necho \"  User: $(whoami)\"\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"\"\n\n# --- [1] OpenClaw Platform Audit ---\necho \"=== [1] OpenClaw Platform Audit ===\"\nif command -v openclaw &>/dev/null; then\n    OC_VERSION=$(openclaw --version 2>&1)\n    echo \"Version: $OC_VERSION\"\n    \n    AUDIT_OUTPUT=$(openclaw security audit 2>&1) || true\n    if [[ -n \"$AUDIT_OUTPUT\" ]]; then\n        AUDIT_OUTPUT=$(apply_exclusions \"platform_audit\" \"$AUDIT_OUTPUT\")\n        echo \"$AUDIT_OUTPUT\"\n        if echo \"$AUDIT_OUTPUT\" | grep -qi \"critical\\|high\\|fail\" | grep -v \"\\[已知问题-忽略\"; then\n            count_critical\n        elif echo \"$AUDIT_OUTPUT\" | grep -qi \"warn\" | grep -v \"\\[已知问题-忽略\"; then\n            count_warn\n        else\n            count_ok\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"✅ openclaw security audit passed with no findings\"\n        count_ok\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: openclaw command not found!\"\n    count_critical\nfi\necho \"\"\n\n# Hmm, actually `openclaw security audit` might not exist. Let me check...\n# I should make the script robust - try the command and handle if it doesn't exist.\n\n# Let me rethink this. The script needs to be practical. Let me write a cleaner version.\n```\n\nLet me rewrite this more carefully. I'll make it robust and handle cases where commands might not exist.\n\nActually, for the `openclaw security audit` command - I'm not sure if this exists in the current version. Let me make the script handle that gracefully.\n\nAlso, I need to think about the grep logic for known issues - the pipe approach above is wrong. Let me fix the pattern matching.\n\nLet me write a cleaner, more reliable script:\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -uo pipefail\n\nOC=\"${OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR:-$HOME/.openclaw}\"\nREPORT_DIR=\"$OC/security-reports\"\nKNOWN_ISSUES_FILE=\"$OC/.security-audit-known-issues.json\"\nTIMESTAMP=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')\nREPORT_FILE=\"$REPORT_DIR/audit-${TIMESTAMP}.txt\"\n\nCRITICAL=0\nWARN=0\nOK=0\n\nmkdir -p \"$REPORT_DIR\"\n\ninc_c() { CRITICAL=$((CRITICAL + 1)); }\ninc_w() { WARN=$((WARN + 1)); }\ninc_o() { OK=$((OK + 1)); }\n\n# Filter known issues: reads stdin, marks lines matching patterns for given check\nfilter_known() {\n    local check=\"$1\"\n    if [[ ! -f \"$KNOWN_ISSUES_FILE\" ]] || [[ ! -s \"$KNOWN_ISSUES_FILE\" ]]; then\n        cat\n        return\n    fi\n    \n    # Build a temp file with patterns\n    local tmpfile\n    tmpfile=$(mktemp)\n    python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('$KNOWN_ISSUES_FILE') as f:\n    issues = json.load(f)\nfor i in issues:\n    if i.get('check') == '$check':\n        print(i['pattern'] + '\\t' + i.get('reason', 'known'))\n\" > \"$tmpfile\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    \n    if [[ ! -s \"$tmpfile\" ]]; then\n        rm -f \"$tmpfile\"\n        cat\n        return\n    fi\n    \n    while IFS= read -r line; do\n        local matched=0\n        while IFS=$'\\t' read -r pat reason; do\n            if echo \"$line\" | grep -qiE \"$pat\"; then\n                echo \"[已知问题-忽略: $reason] $line\"\n                matched=1\n                break\n            fi\n        done < \"$tmpfile\"\n        [[ $matched -eq 0 ]] && echo \"$line\"\n    done\n    rm -f \"$tmpfile\"\n}\n\n# Count issues in output (excluding known issues)\ncount_issues() {\n    local output=\"$1\"\n    local critical_count warn_count\n    critical_count=$(echo \"$output\" | grep -ciE \"critical|🚨|CRITICAL\" | grep -cv \"\\[已知问题-忽略\" || echo 0)\n    # This approach is wrong too... let me think differently\n}\n```\n\nOK, I'm overcomplicating this. Let me take a step back and write a clean, practical script.\n\nKey decisions:\n1. Each check section outputs its findings\n2. At the end of each section, we count based on what was found\n3. Known issues filtering is done inline\n4. The script should work with basic tools (no python dependency for core functionality)\n\nActually, using python3 for JSON parsing of known issues is reasonable since it's likely available. But let me make it optional.\n\nLet me write the final version now. I'll be practical and thorough.\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# ============================================================\n# nightly-security-audit.sh\n# OpenClaw 极简安全实践指南 v2.8 — 夜间安全巡检脚本\n# Generated: 2026-04-02 by 樱桃 (Cherry) 🍒\n# ============================================================\nset -uo pipefail\n\n# --- Config ---\nOC=\"${OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR:-$HOME/.openclaw}\"\nREPORT_DIR=\"$OC/security-reports\"\nKNOWN_ISSUES=\"$OC/.security-audit-known-issues.json\"\nBASELINE_CONFIG=\"$OC/.config-baseline.sha256\"\nBASELINE_SKILL=\"$OC/.skill-baseline.sha256\"\nTIMESTAMP=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')\nREPORT=\"$REPORT_DIR/audit-${TIMESTAMP}.txt\"\n\nCRITICAL=0; WARN=0; OK_COUNT=0\n\nmkdir -p \"$REPORT_DIR\"\n\n# --- Helpers ---\ninc_c() { CRITICAL=$((CRITICAL + 1)); }\ninc_w() { WARN=$((WARN + 1)); }\ninc_o() { OK_COUNT=$((OK_COUNT + 1)); }\n\nheader() { echo \"\"; echo \"=== [$1] $2 ===\"; }\n\n# Filter known issues from piped input for a specific check\nfilter_known_issues() {\n    local check_name=\"$1\"\n    if [[ ! -f \"$KNOWN_ISSUES\" ]] || ! command -v python3 &>/dev/null; then\n        cat; return\n    fi\n    python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json, re\ntry:\n    with open('$KNOWN_ISSUES') as f:\n        issues = json.load(f)\nexcept:\n    issues = []\npatterns = [(i['pattern'], i.get('reason','known issue')) for i in issues if i.get('check')=='$check_name']\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.rstrip('\\n')\n    matched = False\n    for pat, reason in patterns:\n        if re.search(pat, line, re.IGNORECASE):\n            print(f'[已知问题-忽略: {reason}] {line}')\n            matched = True\n            break\n    if not matched:\n        print(line)\n\" 2>/dev/null || cat\n}\n\n# --- Begin Report ---\n{\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"  OpenClaw Nightly Security Audit Report\"\necho \"  Time : $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')\"\necho \"  Host : $(hostname)\"\necho \"  User : $(whoami)\"\necho \"=============================================\"\n\n# =============================================\n# [1] OpenClaw Platform Audit\n# =============================================\nheader 1 \"OpenClaw Platform Audit\"\nif command -v openclaw &>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"Version: $(openclaw --version 2>&1)\"\n    GW_STATUS=$(openclaw gateway status 2>&1 | head -n 20) || true\n    echo \"$GW_STATUS\"\n    if echo \"$GW_STATUS\" | grep -qi \"running\\|active\"; then\n        echo \"✅ Gateway is running\"\n        inc_o\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Gateway may not be running\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: openclaw command not found!\"\n    inc_c\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [2] Process & Network Audit\n# =============================================\nheader 2 \"Process & Network Audit\"\n\necho \"--- Listening Ports (TCP) ---\"\nTCP_LISTEN=$(sudo ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null || ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null || echo \"ss command failed\")\necho \"$TCP_LISTEN\" | head -n 30\nTCP_COUNT=$(echo \"$TCP_LISTEN\" | grep -c \"LISTEN\" || echo 0)\necho \"(Total TCP listeners: $TCP_COUNT)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- Listening Ports (UDP) ---\"\nUDP_LISTEN=$(sudo ss -ulnp 2>/dev/null || ss -ulnp 2>/dev/null || echo \"ss command failed\")\necho \"$UDP_LISTEN\" | head -n 20\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Outbound Connections ---\"\nOUTBOUND=$(sudo ss -tnp 2>/dev/null || ss -tnp 2>/dev/null || echo \"ss command failed\")\necho \"$OUTBOUND\" | grep -v \"127.0.0.1.*127.0.0.1\\|::1.*::1\" | head -n 30\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Top 15 Processes by CPU ---\"\nps aux --sort=-%cpu | head -n 16\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Top 15 Processes by Memory ---\"\nps aux --sort=-%mem | head -n 16\n\n# Simple heuristic: if there are outbound connections to unusual ports, warn\nSUSPICIOUS_OUT=$(echo \"$OUTBOUND\" | grep -vE \":(443|80|53|22|8080|18789|8443) \" | grep \"ESTAB\" | grep -v \"127.0.0.1\\|::1\" | head -n 10)\nif [[ -n \"$SUSPICIOUS_OUT\" ]]; then\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Outbound connections to non-standard ports detected:\"\n    echo \"$SUSPICIOUS_OUT\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"✅ No suspicious outbound connections detected\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [3] Sensitive Directory Changes (24h)\n# =============================================\nheader 3 \"Sensitive Directory Changes (24h)\"\nDIRS_TO_CHECK=(\"$OC\" \"/etc\" \"$HOME/.ssh\" \"$HOME/.gnupg\" \"/usr/local/bin\")\nTOTAL_CHANGES=0\nfor dir in \"${DIRS_TO_CHECK[@]}\"; do\n    if [[ -d \"$dir\" ]]; then\n        CHANGES=$(find \"$dir\" -maxdepth 3 -mtime -1 -type f 2>/dev/null | head -n 50)\n        COUNT=$(echo \"$CHANGES\" | grep -c \".\" || echo 0)\n        if [[ -n \"$CHANGES\" ]] && [[ \"$COUNT\" -gt 0 ]]; then\n            echo \"--- $dir ($COUNT files changed) ---\"\n            echo \"$CHANGES\" | filter_known_issues \"dir_changes\"\n            TOTAL_CHANGES=$((TOTAL_CHANGES + COUNT))\n        else\n            echo \"--- $dir (no changes) ---\"\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"--- $dir (directory not found, skipped) ---\"\n    fi\ndone\nif [[ $TOTAL_CHANGES -gt 20 ]]; then\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: $TOTAL_CHANGES files changed in sensitive dirs in last 24h\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ $TOTAL_CHANGES file(s) changed in sensitive dirs (within normal range)\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [4] System Scheduled Tasks\n# =============================================\nheader 4 \"System Scheduled Tasks\"\necho \"--- User crontab ---\"\nCRONTAB_OUT=$(crontab -l 2>&1) || true\nif [[ \"$CRONTAB_OUT\" == *\"no crontab\"* ]]; then\n    echo \"(no user crontab)\"\nelse\n    echo \"$CRONTAB_OUT\"\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- /etc/cron.d/ ---\"\nls -la /etc/cron.d/ 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- systemd timers (system) ---\"\nsystemctl list-timers --all 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- systemd timers (user) ---\"\nsystemctl --user list-timers --all 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- User systemd units (~/.config/systemd/user/) ---\"\nif [[ -d \"$HOME/.config/systemd/user\" ]]; then\n    ls -la \"$HOME/.config/systemd/user/\" 2>/dev/null | head -n 20\nelse\n    echo \"(no user systemd units directory)\"\nfi\necho \"✅ Scheduled tasks listed for review\"\ninc_o\n\n# =============================================\n# [5] OpenClaw Cron Jobs\n# =============================================\nheader 5 \"OpenClaw Cron Jobs\"\nOC_CRON=$(openclaw cron list 2>&1) || true\necho \"$OC_CRON\" | head -n 30\necho \"✅ OpenClaw cron jobs listed for review\"\ninc_o\n\n# =============================================\n# [6] Login & SSH\n# =============================================\nheader 6 \"Login & SSH\"\necho \"--- Recent logins ---\"\nlast -n 20 2>/dev/null || echo \"(last command not available)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- SSH auth failures (last 24h) ---\"\nSSH_FAILS=$(sudo journalctl -u sshd -u ssh --since \"24 hours ago\" 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"fail\\|invalid\\|refused\" | tail -n 100) || true\nif [[ -n \"$SSH_FAILS\" ]]; then\n    FAIL_COUNT=$(echo \"$SSH_FAILS\" | wc -l)\n    echo \"$SSH_FAILS\" | tail -n 20\n    echo \"(Total failures in 24h: $FAIL_COUNT)\"\n    if [[ $FAIL_COUNT -gt 50 ]]; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: $FAIL_COUNT SSH failures — possible brute force!\"\n        inc_c\n    elif [[ $FAIL_COUNT -gt 10 ]]; then\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: $FAIL_COUNT SSH failures\"\n        inc_w\n    else\n        echo \"✅ SSH failures within normal range ($FAIL_COUNT)\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No SSH authentication failures in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [7] Critical File Integrity\n# =============================================\nheader 7 \"Critical File Integrity\"\n\necho \"--- Config hash baseline check ---\"\nif [[ -f \"$BASELINE_CONFIG\" ]]; then\n    HASH_CHECK=$(sha256sum -c \"$BASELINE_CONFIG\" 2>&1)\n    echo \"$HASH_CHECK\"\n    if echo \"$HASH_CHECK\" | grep -q \"FAILED\"; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Config file hash mismatch!\"\n        inc_c\n    else\n        echo \"✅ Config hash baseline intact\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: No config baseline file found at $BASELINE_CONFIG\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- File permissions check ---\"\nFILES_TO_CHECK=(\n    \"$OC/openclaw.json:600\"\n    \"$OC/devices/paired.json:600\"\n)\n# Add SSH files if they exist\n[[ -f \"$HOME/.ssh/authorized_keys\" ]] && FILES_TO_CHECK+=(\"$HOME/.ssh/authorized_keys:600\")\n[[ -f \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" ]] && FILES_TO_CHECK+=(\"/etc/ssh/sshd_config:644\")\n\nPERM_OK=true\nfor entry in \"${FILES_TO_CHECK[@]}\"; do\n    filepath=\"${entry%%:*}\"\n    expected=\"${entry##*:}\"\n    if [[ -f \"$filepath\" ]]; then\n        actual=$(stat -c '%a' \"$filepath\" 2>/dev/null)\n        if [[ \"$actual\" == \"$expected\" ]]; then\n            echo \"  ✅ $filepath ($actual)\"\n        else\n            echo \"  🚨 $filepath expected=$expected actual=$actual\"\n            PERM_OK=false\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"  ⚠️ $filepath (not found)\"\n    fi\ndone\nif $PERM_OK; then\n    inc_o\nelse\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Permission mismatch detected!\"\n    inc_c\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [8] Yellow-Line Cross Validation\n# =============================================\nheader 8 \"Yellow-Line Cross Validation\"\necho \"--- sudo commands in auth.log (last 24h) ---\"\n\n# Get sudo commands, exclude audit script's own sudo calls\nSUDO_LOG=\"\"\nif [[ -f /var/log/auth.log ]]; then\n    SUDO_LOG=$(sudo grep \"sudo\" /var/log/auth.log 2>/dev/null | tail -n 50 | grep -vE \"ss -|journalctl|grep|head|tail|cat|sha256sum|find.*mtime|stat \" || true)\nelif command -v journalctl &>/dev/null; then\n    SUDO_LOG=$(sudo journalctl --since \"24 hours ago\" 2>/dev/null | grep \"sudo\" | tail -n 50 | grep -vE \"ss -|journalctl|grep|head|tail|cat|sha256sum|find.*mtime|stat \" || true)\nfi\n\nif [[ -n \"$SUDO_LOG\" ]]; then\n    echo \"$SUDO_LOG\" | head -n 30\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"--- Memory yellow-line entries ---\"\n    if [[ -f \"$TODAY_MEMORY\" ]]; then\n        grep -i \"黄线\\|yellow.line\\|sudo\" \"$TODAY_MEMORY\" 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(no yellow-line entries in today's memory)\"\n    else\n        echo \"(today's memory file not found)\"\n    fi\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: sudo commands found — verify against memory logs\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No non-audit sudo commands detected in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [9] Disk Usage\n# =============================================\nheader 9 \"Disk Usage\"\necho \"--- Overall usage ---\"\nDF_OUT=$(df -h / 2>/dev/null)\necho \"$DF_OUT\"\nUSAGE_PCT=$(df / 2>/dev/null | tail -1 | awk '{print $5}' | tr -d '%')\nif [[ -n \"$USAGE_PCT\" ]] && [[ $USAGE_PCT -gt 85 ]]; then\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT}% (>85%)\"\n    inc_c\nelif [[ -n \"$USAGE_PCT\" ]] && [[ $USAGE_PCT -gt 70 ]]; then\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT}%\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT:-unknown}%\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- Large files created in last 24h (>100MB) ---\"\nLARGE_FILES=$(find / -maxdepth 5 -mtime -1 -size +100M -type f 2>/dev/null | head -n 20)\nif [[ -n \"$LARGE_FILES\" ]]; then\n    echo \"$LARGE_FILES\"\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Large files detected\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No large files (>100MB) created in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [10] Gateway Environment Variables\n# =============================================\nheader 10 \"Gateway Environment Variables\"\nGW_PID=$(pgrep -f \"openclaw.*gateway\\|openclaw-gateway\" | head -1) || true\nif [[ -n \"$GW_PID\" ]]; then\n    echo \"Gateway PID: $GW_PID\"\n    ENV_SENSITIVE=$(sudo cat \"/proc/$GW_PID/environ\" 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep -iE \"KEY|TOKEN|SECRET|PASSWORD|API\" | sed 's/=.*/=***REDACTED***/' | sort) || true\n    if [[ -n \"$ENV_SENSITIVE\" ]]; then\n        echo \"$ENV_SENSITIVE\" | filter_known_issues \"gateway_env\"\n        # Count non-excluded items\n        UNEXCLUDED=$(echo \"$ENV_SENSITIVE\" | filter_known_issues \"gateway_env\" | grep -cv \"\\[已知问题-忽略\" || echo 0)\n        if [[ $UNEXCLUDED -gt 0 ]]; then\n            echo \"⚠️ WARN: Review sensitive env vars above\"\n            inc_w\n        else\n            echo \"✅ All sensitive env vars are in known list\"\n            inc_o\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"✅ No sensitive environment variables detected (or process not readable)\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Gateway process not found (not running?)\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [11] DLP - Plaintext Key/Credential Scan\n# =============================================\nheader 11 \"DLP Scan (Plaintext Keys/Credentials)\"\nSCAN_DIRS=(\"$OC/workspace/memory\" \"$OC/workspace/logs\" \"$OC/workspace\")\nDLP_HITS=\"\"\nfor dir in \"${SCAN_DIRS[@]}\"; do\n    [[ ! -d \"$dir\" ]] && continue\n    # Scan for private keys, mnemonics, etc. Exclude known safe dirs\n    HITS=$(grep -rlE \"(-----BEGIN (RSA |EC |OPENSSH )?PRIVATE KEY-----|([a-f0-9]{64})|(\\b(abandon|ability|able|about|above|absent)\\b.*\\b(word|wolf|woman|wonder|wood|wool)\\b))\" \\\n        \"$dir\" --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.txt\" --include=\"*.json\" --include=\"*.log\" --include=\"*.yaml\" --include=\"*.yml\" \\\n        2>/dev/null | grep -vE \"advisories/|example|test|node_modules\" | head -n 20) || true\n    [[ -n \"$HITS\" ]] && DLP_HITS=\"${DLP_HITS}${HITS}\\n\"\ndone\n\nif [[ -n \"$DLP_HITS\" ]]; then\n    echo \"Files with potential credential matches:\"\n    echo -e \"$DLP_HITS\" | filter_known_issues \"dlp_scan\"\n    REAL_HITS=$(echo -e \"$DLP_HITS\" | filter_known_issues \"dlp_scan\" | grep -cv \"\\[已知问题-忽略\" || echo 0)\n    if [[ $REAL_HITS -gt 0 ]]; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Potential plaintext credentials found! (files listed above — values NOT printed for safety)\"\n        inc_c\n    else\n        echo \"✅ All DLP matches are known/excluded\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No plaintext private keys or credentials detected\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [12] Skill/MCP Integrity\n# =============================================\nheader 12 \"Skill/MCP Integrity\"\nSKILL_DIR=\"$OC/workspace/skills\"\nif [[ -d \"$SKILL_DIR\" ]] && [[ \"$(ls -A \"$SKILL_DIR\" 2>/dev/null)\" ]]; then\n    CURRENT_HASH=$(find \"$SKILL_DIR\" -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' -exec sha256sum {} \\; 2>/dev/null | sort | sha256sum | awk '{print $1}')\n    echo \"Current skill hash: $CURRENT_HASH\"\n    if [[ -f \"$BASELINE_SKILL\" ]]; then\n        BASELINE_HASH=$(cat \"$BASELINE_SKILL\" | awk '{print $1}')\n        echo \"Baseline skill hash: $BASELINE_HASH\"\n        if [[ \"$CURRENT_HASH\" == \"$BASELINE_HASH\" ]]; then\n            echo \"✅ Skill/MCP integrity verified — no changes\"\n            inc_o\n        else\n            echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Skill files changed since last baseline!\"\n            echo \"Run: find $SKILL_DIR -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' -mtime -1 | to check recent changes\"\n            inc_c\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: No skill baseline found at $BASELINE_SKILL\"\n        echo \"Run: find $SKILL_DIR -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' -exec sha256sum {} \\\\; | sort | sha256sum > $BASELINE_SKILL\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No skills installed (directory empty or missing)\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# [13] Brain Backup (Git)\n# =============================================\nheader 13 \"Brain Backup (Git Sync)\"\nif (cd \"$OC\" && git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree &>/dev/null); then\n    echo \"Git repo detected in $OC\"\n    # Check for remote\n    REMOTE=$(cd \"$OC\" && git remote -v 2>/dev/null | head -n 2)\n    if [[ -n \"$REMOTE\" ]]; then\n        echo \"$REMOTE\"\n        # Attempt auto commit + push\n        cd \"$OC\"\n        git add -A 2>/dev/null || true\n        CHANGES=$(git diff --cached --stat 2>/dev/null)\n        if [[ -n \"$CHANGES\" ]]; then\n            echo \"Changes to commit:\"\n            echo \"$CHANGES\"\n            git commit -m \"nightly-audit: auto-backup $(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\" 2>/dev/null || true\n            if git push 2>&1 | tail -n 5; then\n                echo \"✅ Brain backup pushed successfully\"\n                inc_o\n            else\n                echo \"⚠️ WARN: Git push failed (check credentials/remote)\"\n                inc_w\n            fi\n        else\n            echo \"✅ No changes to backup\"\n            inc_o\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Git repo exists but no remote configured\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ No git repo in $OC — brain backup not configured\"\n    echo \"(This is optional; set up with: cd $OC && git init && git remote add origin <url>)\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\n# =============================================\n# Summary\n# =============================================\necho \"\"\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"Summary: $CRITICAL critical · $WARN warn · $OK_COUNT ok\"\necho \"Report saved: $REPORT\"\necho \"=============================================\"\n\n} | tee \"$REPORT\"\n\n# Hmm, the tee approach has a problem with the curly braces and the earlier tee...\n```\n\nWait, I'm making an error with the output redirection. Let me simplify. The report should be written to the file AND to stdout. The simplest approach is to use `tee` at the script level or use a function.\n\nActually, a cleaner approach: just write everything to stdout, and at the end redirect everything. Or use `exec > >(tee \"$REPORT\") 2>&1` at the top.\n\nBut the script is called by the cron agent, which will read stdout. So the approach should be:\n1. All output goes to stdout\n2. We also capture everything to the report file\n\nUsing `exec > >(tee \"$REPORT_FILE\") 2>&1` at the beginning is the simplest.\n\nBut wait, the counter variables won't work correctly inside a pipe/subshell with tee. Let me think...\n\nActually, `>(tee ...)` with process substitution should be fine because the main script still runs in the same shell. The `tee` is just reading from the pipe. The counter variables are in the main shell.\n\nLet me restructure:\n\n```bash\nexec > >(tee \"$REPORT_FILE\") 2>&1\n\n# ... all echo/commands ...\n\n# At the end, the summary line\necho \"Summary: $CRITICAL critical · $WARN warn · $OK_COUNT ok\"\n```\n\nThis should work. The `tee` gets all stdout and writes to both the terminal (which the cron agent reads) and the file.\n\nOne concern: the `exec > >(tee ...)` might not flush properly before the script exits. I can add a `wait` at the end.\n\nLet me also reconsider the DLP regex. The mnemonic detection regex I wrote is too simplistic. A better approach would be to check for lines with 12 or 24 common BIP39 words. But that's complex. Let me use a simpler heuristic:\n- Check for private key headers\n- Check for hex strings that look like private keys (0x followed by 64 hex chars)\n- Check for patterns that look like 12/24 word sequences\n\nActually, for the DLP scan, let me keep it practical:\n1. Private key file headers: `-----BEGIN.*PRIVATE KEY-----`\n2. Ethereum-style private keys: `0x[a-f0-9]{64}`\n3. For mnemonics, just look for files containing many BIP39 words in sequence - but this is hard in bash. Let me just check for the pattern of 12+ lowercase words separated by spaces on a single line, which is a common mnemonic format.\n\nAlso, I need to be careful about what I print. Even if we find credentials, we should NOT print the actual values, just the file paths.\n\nLet me also reconsider the script structure. The find for large files searching from `/` with maxdepth 5 will be slow. Let me limit to home and key directories.\n\nOK let me write the final clean version. I'll keep it practical and well-tested.\n\nAlso I just realized I should check if the `openclaw security audit` command actually exists. Let me handle that gracefully.\n\nOne more thing - for item [8] Yellow-Line Cross Validation, in WSL the auth.log might not exist. Let me handle that.\n\nFor item [2] process/network, `sudo ss` might need approval. Since this runs in a cron isolated session... the exec approval could be a problem. Let me write the script to try with sudo first, fall back to non-sudo.\n\nActually wait - the script itself runs via `bash script.sh`, not through the exec tool. If the cron agent runs `bash /path/to/script.sh` through exec, the entire script is one command. The sudo calls inside the script would need the user's password (or NOPASSWD sudoers rule).\n\nIn WSL, the user might have passwordless sudo. Let me write the script to try sudo but not fail if it doesn't work.\n\nOK, let me finalize the script now. I'll also handle the TODAY_MEMORY variable correctly.\n\nActually, one important thing from the guide: \"脚本开头使用 `set -uo pipefail`（不要用 `set -e`——单项检查失败不应中断整个审计流程）\"\n\nThis is important - I should NOT use `set -e`.\n\nLet me now write the complete script carefully. I'll avoid all the pitfalls.\n\nAlso for DLP, the guide says: \"即使查出真实泄露，推送到频道的简报也必须经过打码如 0x12...abcd 处理\" - but since we're only saving locally and the summary is generated by the LLM, I should just print file paths, not values.\n\nOK here's my final approach. Let me write it.\n\nFor the cron registration, since there's no messaging channel, I'll use the cron tool directly. The delivery mode will be \"none\" since reports are local only. Actually, I still need the isolated session to run the script and generate the summary. But without a channel to push to... \n\nActually, looking at the user's request: \"检测报告存在本地\" - they want reports saved locally. But the cron job still needs to run the script. I can set up the cron to run the script, and the report gets saved to the security-reports directory automatically by the script itself. The cron delivery can be \"none\" since there's no channel to announce to.\n\nWait, but the point of the cron is to have the agent run the script and generate a human-readable summary. Even without a push channel, having the cron run and save the report locally is still valuable. And if they later add a channel, we can update the delivery.\n\nLet me set up the cron with delivery mode \"none\" for now.\n\nActually, looking at the cron tool API:\n```\n\"delivery\": { \"mode\": \"none|announce|webhook\", ... }\n```\n\nI'll use `delivery.mode = \"none\"`.\n\nFor the cron, I need:\n- schedule: `0 3 * * *` in Asia/Shanghai\n- payload: agentTurn with the message to execute the script\n- sessionTarget: isolated\n- delivery: none (local only)\n\nLet me now write everything.\n\nAlso, I realize I need to generate the skill baseline too, even if there are no skills yet. Let me check if the skills directory exists.\n\nAnd I need to handle the `TODAY_MEMORY` variable in the script - it should reference the date when the script runs, not when it's written.\n\nLet me put it all together now. First write the script, then the known issues JSON, then create necessary dirs, register the cron, lock the script, and finally create the daily memory entry.\n\nLet me write a clean, complete script. I'll split it into the file write."},{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Step 2 完成！** 哈希基线已生成。\n\n现在进入重头戏 — **Step 3：编写巡检脚本 + 注册 Cron**。这个脚本覆盖 13 项核心指标，我先写好文件。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01H1GrNtCq368PvEr735vG3C","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p \"$HOME/.openclaw/security-reports\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/scripts\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"opencode","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":10094,"cacheRead":29663,"cacheWrite":8861,"totalTokens":48621,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.25235,"cacheRead":0.0148315,"cacheWrite":0.05538125,"total":0.32257775}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775115583562,"responseId":"msg_bdrk_0133fXwUc8Pa9Bi54J9UJq7H"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0dac81f1","parentId":"e26cdf9d","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:43:27.685Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01H1GrNtCq368PvEr735vG3C","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Approval required (id 393d71c0, full 393d71c0-2953-42e1-9027-05d92d55c7fa).\nHost: gateway\nCWD: /home/gaoweiwei/.openclaw/workspace\nCommand:\n```sh\nmkdir -p \"$HOME/.openclaw/security-reports\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/scripts\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory\"\n```\nMode: foreground (interactive approvals available).\nBackground mode requires pre-approved policy (allow-always or ask=off).\nReply with: /approve 393d71c0 allow-once|allow-always|deny\nIf the short code is ambiguous, use the full id in /approve."}],"details":{"status":"approval-pending","approvalId":"393d71c0-2953-42e1-9027-05d92d55c7fa","approvalSlug":"393d71c0","expiresAtMs":1775117607676,"host":"gateway","command":"mkdir -p \"$HOME/.openclaw/security-reports\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/scripts\" \"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace/memory\"","cwd":"/home/gaoweiwei/.openclaw/workspace","warningText":""},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775115807678}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e7b48a6","parentId":"0dac81f1","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:45:44.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"在等批准的同时，我先把脚本文件写好："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Foaqy8gXhyv8Xmt15oLoGQ","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/gaoweiwei/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/nightly-security-audit.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# ============================================================\n# nightly-security-audit.sh\n# OpenClaw 极简安全实践指南 v2.8 — 夜间安全巡检脚本\n# Generated: 2026-04-02 by 樱桃 (Cherry) 🍒\n# ============================================================\nset -uo pipefail\n\n# --- Configuration ---\nOC=\"${OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR:-$HOME/.openclaw}\"\nREPORT_DIR=\"$OC/security-reports\"\nKNOWN_ISSUES=\"$OC/.security-audit-known-issues.json\"\nBASELINE_CONFIG=\"$OC/.config-baseline.sha256\"\nBASELINE_SKILL=\"$OC/.skill-baseline.sha256\"\nTIMESTAMP=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')\nREPORT_FILE=\"$REPORT_DIR/audit-${TIMESTAMP}.txt\"\nTODAY_MEMORY=\"$OC/workspace/memory/$(date '+%Y-%m-%d').md\"\n\n# --- Counters ---\nCRITICAL=0\nWARN=0\nOK_COUNT=0\n\ninc_c() { CRITICAL=$((CRITICAL + 1)); }\ninc_w() { WARN=$((WARN + 1)); }\ninc_o() { OK_COUNT=$((OK_COUNT + 1)); }\n\nheader() { printf '\\n=== [%s] %s ===\\n' \"$1\" \"$2\"; }\n\n# --- Create report dir ---\nmkdir -p \"$REPORT_DIR\"\n\n# --- Known Issues Filter ---\n# Reads stdin, marks lines matching known-issue patterns for the given check\nfilter_known_issues() {\n    local check_name=\"$1\"\n    if [[ ! -f \"$KNOWN_ISSUES\" ]] || [[ ! -s \"$KNOWN_ISSUES\" ]] || ! command -v python3 &>/dev/null; then\n        cat\n        return\n    fi\n    python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json, re\ntry:\n    with open('${KNOWN_ISSUES}') as f:\n        issues = json.load(f)\nexcept Exception:\n    issues = []\npatterns = [(i['pattern'], i.get('reason', 'known issue'))\n            for i in issues if i.get('check') == '${check_name}']\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    line = line.rstrip('\\n')\n    matched = False\n    for pat, reason in patterns:\n        try:\n            if re.search(pat, line, re.IGNORECASE):\n                print(f'[已知问题-忽略: {reason}] {line}')\n                matched = True\n                break\n        except re.error:\n            pass\n    if not matched:\n        print(line)\n\" 2>/dev/null || cat\n}\n\n# Count non-excluded lines in input\ncount_real_issues() {\n    grep -cv \"\\[已知问题-忽略\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\"\n}\n\n# --- Redirect all output to tee → report file + stdout ---\nexec > >(tee \"$REPORT_FILE\") 2>&1\n\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"  OpenClaw Nightly Security Audit Report\"\necho \"  Time : $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')\"\necho \"  Host : $(hostname)\"\necho \"  User : $(whoami)\"\necho \"=============================================\"\n\n# =============================================================\n# [1] OpenClaw Platform Audit\n# =============================================================\nheader 1 \"OpenClaw Platform Audit\"\nif command -v openclaw &>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"Version: $(openclaw --version 2>&1)\"\n    GW_STATUS=$(openclaw gateway status 2>&1 | head -n 20) || true\n    echo \"$GW_STATUS\"\n    if echo \"$GW_STATUS\" | grep -qiE \"running|active|online\"; then\n        echo \"✅ Gateway is running\"\n        inc_o\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Gateway may not be running\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: openclaw command not found!\"\n    inc_c\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [2] Process & Network Audit\n# =============================================================\nheader 2 \"Process & Network Audit\"\n\necho \"--- Listening Ports (TCP) ---\"\nTCP_LISTEN=$(sudo ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null || ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null || echo \"[ss failed]\")\necho \"$TCP_LISTEN\" | head -n 30\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Listening Ports (UDP) ---\"\nUDP_LISTEN=$(sudo ss -ulnp 2>/dev/null || ss -ulnp 2>/dev/null || echo \"[ss failed]\")\necho \"$UDP_LISTEN\" | head -n 20\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Outbound Established Connections ---\"\nOUTBOUND=$(sudo ss -tnp state established 2>/dev/null || ss -tnp state established 2>/dev/null || echo \"[ss failed]\")\nOUTBOUND_EXT=$(echo \"$OUTBOUND\" | grep -vE \"127\\.0\\.0\\.1.*127\\.0\\.0\\.1|::1.*::1|\\[::1\\].*\\[::1\\]\" || true)\necho \"$OUTBOUND_EXT\" | head -n 30\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Top 15 by CPU ---\"\nps aux --sort=-%cpu 2>/dev/null | head -n 16\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- Top 15 by Memory ---\"\nps aux --sort=-%mem 2>/dev/null | head -n 16\n\n# Check for suspicious outbound\nSUSPICIOUS=$(echo \"$OUTBOUND_EXT\" | grep -vE \":(443|80|53|22|8080|18789|8443|993|587|465) \" 2>/dev/null \\\n    | grep -v \"^$\\|^Netid\\|^State\" | head -n 10) || true\nif [[ -n \"$SUSPICIOUS\" ]]; then\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Outbound connections to non-standard ports:\"\n    echo \"$SUSPICIOUS\" | filter_known_issues \"network\"\n    REAL=$(echo \"$SUSPICIOUS\" | filter_known_issues \"network\" | count_real_issues)\n    if [[ \"$REAL\" -gt 0 ]]; then inc_w; else inc_o; fi\nelse\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"✅ No suspicious outbound connections\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [3] Sensitive Directory Changes (24h)\n# =============================================================\nheader 3 \"Sensitive Directory Changes (24h)\"\nDIRS_TO_CHECK=(\"$OC\" \"/etc\" \"$HOME/.ssh\" \"$HOME/.gnupg\" \"/usr/local/bin\")\nTOTAL_CHANGES=0\n\nfor dir in \"${DIRS_TO_CHECK[@]}\"; do\n    if [[ -d \"$dir\" ]]; then\n        CHANGES=$(find \"$dir\" -maxdepth 3 -mtime -1 -type f 2>/dev/null | head -n 50)\n        COUNT=0\n        [[ -n \"$CHANGES\" ]] && COUNT=$(echo \"$CHANGES\" | wc -l)\n        echo \"--- $dir ($COUNT file(s) changed) ---\"\n        if [[ $COUNT -gt 0 ]]; then\n            echo \"$CHANGES\" | filter_known_issues \"dir_changes\"\n            TOTAL_CHANGES=$((TOTAL_CHANGES + COUNT))\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"--- $dir (not found, skipped) ---\"\n    fi\ndone\n\nif [[ $TOTAL_CHANGES -gt 50 ]]; then\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: $TOTAL_CHANGES files changed in sensitive dirs\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ $TOTAL_CHANGES file(s) changed in sensitive dirs (normal range)\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [4] System Scheduled Tasks\n# =============================================================\nheader 4 \"System Scheduled Tasks\"\n\necho \"--- User crontab ---\"\nCRONTAB_OUT=$(crontab -l 2>&1) || true\nif echo \"$CRONTAB_OUT\" | grep -qi \"no crontab\"; then\n    echo \"(no user crontab)\"\nelse\n    echo \"$CRONTAB_OUT\" | head -n 20\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- /etc/cron.d/ ---\"\nls -la /etc/cron.d/ 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- systemd timers (system) ---\"\nsystemctl list-timers --all --no-pager 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- systemd timers (user) ---\"\nsystemctl --user list-timers --all --no-pager 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 || echo \"(not accessible)\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- User systemd units ---\"\nif [[ -d \"$HOME/.config/systemd/user\" ]]; then\n    ls -la \"$HOME/.config/systemd/user/\" 2>/dev/null | head -n 20\nelse\n    echo \"(no user systemd units directory)\"\nfi\necho \"✅ Scheduled tasks listed for review\"\ninc_o\n\n# =============================================================\n# [5] OpenClaw Cron Jobs\n# =============================================================\nheader 5 \"OpenClaw Cron Jobs\"\nOC_CRON=$(openclaw cron list 2>&1 | head -n 30) || true\nif [[ -n \"$OC_CRON\" ]]; then\n    echo \"$OC_CRON\"\nelse\n    echo \"(no cron jobs or command failed)\"\nfi\necho \"✅ OpenClaw cron jobs listed for review\"\ninc_o\n\n# =============================================================\n# [6] Login & SSH\n# =============================================================\nheader 6 \"Login & SSH\"\n\necho \"--- Recent logins ---\"\nlast -n 15 2>/dev/null || echo \"(last command not available)\"\necho \"\"\n\necho \"--- SSH auth failures (last 24h) ---\"\nSSH_FAILS=\"\"\nif command -v journalctl &>/dev/null; then\n    SSH_FAILS=$(sudo journalctl -u sshd -u ssh --since \"24 hours ago\" --no-pager 2>/dev/null \\\n        | grep -iE \"fail|invalid|refused\" | tail -n 100) || true\nelif [[ -f /var/log/auth.log ]]; then\n    SSH_FAILS=$(sudo grep -iE \"sshd.*(fail|invalid|refused)\" /var/log/auth.log 2>/dev/null | tail -n 100) || true\nfi\n\nif [[ -n \"$SSH_FAILS\" ]]; then\n    FAIL_COUNT=$(echo \"$SSH_FAILS\" | wc -l)\n    echo \"$SSH_FAILS\" | tail -n 20\n    echo \"(Total SSH failures in 24h: $FAIL_COUNT)\"\n    if [[ $FAIL_COUNT -gt 50 ]]; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: $FAIL_COUNT SSH failures — possible brute force!\"\n        inc_c\n    elif [[ $FAIL_COUNT -gt 10 ]]; then\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: $FAIL_COUNT SSH auth failures\"\n        inc_w\n    else\n        echo \"✅ SSH failures within normal range ($FAIL_COUNT)\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No SSH auth failures in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [7] Critical File Integrity\n# =============================================================\nheader 7 \"Critical File Integrity\"\n\necho \"--- Config hash baseline ---\"\nif [[ -f \"$BASELINE_CONFIG\" ]]; then\n    HASH_CHECK=$(sha256sum -c \"$BASELINE_CONFIG\" 2>&1) || true\n    echo \"$HASH_CHECK\"\n    if echo \"$HASH_CHECK\" | grep -q \"FAILED\"; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Config file hash mismatch!\"\n        inc_c\n    else\n        echo \"✅ Config hash baseline intact\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: No config baseline at $BASELINE_CONFIG\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- File permissions ---\"\ndeclare -A EXPECTED_PERMS=(\n    [\"$OC/openclaw.json\"]=\"600\"\n    [\"$OC/devices/paired.json\"]=\"600\"\n)\n[[ -f \"$HOME/.ssh/authorized_keys\" ]] && EXPECTED_PERMS[\"$HOME/.ssh/authorized_keys\"]=\"600\"\n[[ -f \"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\" ]] && EXPECTED_PERMS[\"/etc/ssh/sshd_config\"]=\"644\"\n\nPERM_CLEAN=true\nfor filepath in \"${!EXPECTED_PERMS[@]}\"; do\n    expected=\"${EXPECTED_PERMS[$filepath]}\"\n    if [[ -f \"$filepath\" ]]; then\n        actual=$(stat -c '%a' \"$filepath\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"???\")\n        if [[ \"$actual\" == \"$expected\" ]]; then\n            echo \"  ✅ $filepath (perm=$actual)\"\n        else\n            echo \"  🚨 $filepath expected=$expected actual=$actual\"\n            PERM_CLEAN=false\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"  ⚠️ $filepath (not found)\"\n    fi\ndone\n\nif $PERM_CLEAN; then\n    echo \"✅ All file permissions correct\"\n    inc_o\nelse\n    echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Permission mismatch detected!\"\n    inc_c\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [8] Yellow-Line Cross Validation\n# =============================================================\nheader 8 \"Yellow-Line Cross Validation\"\n\necho \"--- sudo commands in logs (last 24h, excluding audit commands) ---\"\nSUDO_LOG=\"\"\nif [[ -f /var/log/auth.log ]]; then\n    SUDO_LOG=$(sudo grep \"sudo:\" /var/log/auth.log 2>/dev/null \\\n        | grep -v \"pam_unix\" \\\n        | grep -vE \"COMMAND=.*(ss |journalctl|grep |head |tail |cat |sha256sum|find .*mtime|stat |tee )\" \\\n        | tail -n 30) || true\nelif command -v journalctl &>/dev/null; then\n    SUDO_LOG=$(sudo journalctl --since \"24 hours ago\" --no-pager 2>/dev/null \\\n        | grep \"sudo:\" \\\n        | grep -v \"pam_unix\" \\\n        | grep -vE \"COMMAND=.*(ss |journalctl|grep |head |tail |cat |sha256sum|find .*mtime|stat |tee )\" \\\n        | tail -n 30) || true\nfi\n\nif [[ -n \"$SUDO_LOG\" ]]; then\n    echo \"$SUDO_LOG\" | head -n 20\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"--- Memory yellow-line entries (today) ---\"\n    if [[ -f \"$TODAY_MEMORY\" ]]; then\n        grep -iE \"黄线|yellow.line|sudo|\\[yellow\\]\" \"$TODAY_MEMORY\" 2>/dev/null | head -n 20 \\\n            || echo \"(no yellow-line entries in today's memory)\"\n    else\n        echo \"(today's memory file not found)\"\n    fi\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Non-audit sudo commands found — verify against memory logs\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No non-audit sudo commands in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [9] Disk Usage\n# =============================================================\nheader 9 \"Disk Usage\"\n\necho \"--- Overall ---\"\ndf -h / 2>/dev/null || echo \"[df failed]\"\nUSAGE_PCT=$(df / 2>/dev/null | tail -1 | awk '{gsub(/%/,\"\"); print $5}') || true\n\nif [[ -n \"$USAGE_PCT\" ]] && [[ \"$USAGE_PCT\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]]; then\n    if [[ $USAGE_PCT -gt 85 ]]; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT}% (>85%)\"\n        inc_c\n    elif [[ $USAGE_PCT -gt 70 ]]; then\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT}%\"\n        inc_w\n    else\n        echo \"✅ Disk usage at ${USAGE_PCT}%\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Could not determine disk usage\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"--- Large files (>100MB) created in last 24h ---\"\nLARGE_FILES=$(find \"$HOME\" /tmp /var -maxdepth 4 -mtime -1 -size +100M -type f 2>/dev/null | head -n 20) || true\nif [[ -n \"$LARGE_FILES\" ]]; then\n    echo \"$LARGE_FILES\"\n    echo \"⚠️ WARN: Large files detected\"\n    inc_w\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No large files (>100MB) created in last 24h\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [10] Gateway Environment Variables\n# =============================================================\nheader 10 \"Gateway Environment Variables\"\n\nGW_PID=$(pgrep -f \"openclaw.*gateway\\|node.*openclaw\" 2>/dev/null | head -1) || true\nif [[ -n \"$GW_PID\" ]]; then\n    echo \"Gateway PID: $GW_PID\"\n    ENV_SENSITIVE=$(sudo cat \"/proc/$GW_PID/environ\" 2>/dev/null \\\n        | tr '\\0' '\\n' \\\n        | grep -iE \"KEY|TOKEN|SECRET|PASSWORD|API\" \\\n        | sed 's/=.*/=***REDACTED***/' \\\n        | sort) || true\n    if [[ -n \"$ENV_SENSITIVE\" ]]; then\n        FILTERED=$(echo \"$ENV_SENSITIVE\" | filter_known_issues \"gateway_env\")\n        echo \"$FILTERED\"\n        REAL=$(echo \"$FILTERED\" | count_real_issues)\n        if [[ \"$REAL\" -gt 0 ]]; then\n            echo \"⚠️ WARN: Review sensitive env vars above (${REAL} unrecognized)\"\n            inc_w\n        else\n            echo \"✅ All sensitive env vars match known whitelist\"\n            inc_o\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"✅ No sensitive env vars detected (or process not readable)\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    # Try alternative: systemd service\n    GW_PID2=$(systemctl --user show openclaw-gateway -p MainPID --value 2>/dev/null) || true\n    if [[ -n \"$GW_PID2\" ]] && [[ \"$GW_PID2\" != \"0\" ]]; then\n        echo \"Gateway PID (systemd): $GW_PID2\"\n        echo \"(env check skipped — rerun with sudo if needed)\"\n        inc_o\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Gateway process not found\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [11] DLP Scan (Plaintext Keys/Credentials)\n# =============================================================\nheader 11 \"DLP Scan (Plaintext Keys/Credentials)\"\n\nDLP_HITS_FILE=$(mktemp)\nSCAN_DIRS=(\"$OC/workspace\")\n\nfor dir in \"${SCAN_DIRS[@]}\"; do\n    [[ ! -d \"$dir\" ]] && continue\n    # Private key headers\n    grep -rl \"BEGIN.*PRIVATE KEY\" \"$dir\" \\\n        --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.txt\" --include=\"*.json\" \\\n        --include=\"*.log\" --include=\"*.yaml\" --include=\"*.yml\" \\\n        --include=\"*.env\" --include=\"*.conf\" \\\n        2>/dev/null | grep -vE \"node_modules|advisories/|\\.git/\" \\\n        >> \"$DLP_HITS_FILE\" || true\n\n    # Ethereum-style hex private keys (0x + 64 hex chars)\n    grep -rlE \"0x[a-fA-F0-9]{64}\" \"$dir\" \\\n        --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.txt\" --include=\"*.json\" \\\n        --include=\"*.log\" --include=\"*.yaml\" --include=\"*.yml\" \\\n        --include=\"*.env\" --include=\"*.conf\" \\\n        2>/dev/null | grep -vE \"node_modules|advisories/|\\.git/|example|test\" \\\n        >> \"$DLP_HITS_FILE\" || true\n\n    # Mnemonic-like patterns (12+ lowercase words on one line)\n    grep -rlE \"^(\\s*[a-z]{3,10}\\s+){11,}[a-z]{3,10}\\s*$\" \"$dir\" \\\n        --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.txt\" --include=\"*.json\" \\\n        --include=\"*.log\" --include=\"*.env\" \\\n        2>/dev/null | grep -vE \"node_modules|advisories/|\\.git/|example|test\" \\\n        >> \"$DLP_HITS_FILE\" || true\ndone\n\n# Deduplicate\nDLP_UNIQUE=$(sort -u \"$DLP_HITS_FILE\") || true\nrm -f \"$DLP_HITS_FILE\"\n\nif [[ -n \"$DLP_UNIQUE\" ]]; then\n    echo \"Files with potential credential patterns:\"\n    FILTERED_DLP=$(echo \"$DLP_UNIQUE\" | filter_known_issues \"dlp_scan\")\n    echo \"$FILTERED_DLP\"\n    REAL_DLP=$(echo \"$FILTERED_DLP\" | count_real_issues)\n    if [[ \"$REAL_DLP\" -gt 0 ]]; then\n        echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Potential plaintext credentials in ${REAL_DLP} file(s)!\"\n        echo \"(Values NOT printed for safety — inspect files manually)\"\n        inc_c\n    else\n        echo \"✅ All DLP matches are known/excluded\"\n        inc_o\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No plaintext private keys or credential patterns detected\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [12] Skill/MCP Integrity\n# =============================================================\nheader 12 \"Skill/MCP Integrity\"\n\nSKILL_DIR=\"$OC/workspace/skills\"\nif [[ -d \"$SKILL_DIR\" ]] && [[ -n \"$(ls -A \"$SKILL_DIR\" 2>/dev/null)\" ]]; then\n    CURRENT_HASH=$(find \"$SKILL_DIR\" -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' \\\n        -exec sha256sum {} \\; 2>/dev/null | sort | sha256sum | awk '{print $1}')\n    echo \"Current aggregated hash: ${CURRENT_HASH:0:16}...\"\n\n    if [[ -f \"$BASELINE_SKILL\" ]]; then\n        BASELINE_HASH=$(awk '{print $1}' \"$BASELINE_SKILL\")\n        echo \"Baseline hash:          ${BASELINE_HASH:0:16}...\"\n        if [[ \"$CURRENT_HASH\" == \"$BASELINE_HASH\" ]]; then\n            echo \"✅ Skill/MCP integrity verified — no changes\"\n            inc_o\n        else\n            echo \"🚨 CRITICAL: Skill/MCP files changed since last baseline!\"\n            find \"$SKILL_DIR\" -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' -mtime -1 2>/dev/null | head -n 20\n            inc_c\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: No skill baseline at $BASELINE_SKILL\"\n        echo \"  Generate with: find \\$SKILL_DIR -type f -not -path '*/.git/*' -exec sha256sum {} \\\\; | sort | sha256sum > $BASELINE_SKILL\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"✅ No skills installed (directory empty or not found)\"\n    inc_o\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# [13] Brain Backup (Git Sync)\n# =============================================================\nheader 13 \"Brain Backup (Git Sync)\"\n\nif (cd \"$OC\" 2>/dev/null && git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree &>/dev/null); then\n    echo \"Git repo: $OC\"\n    REMOTE_INFO=$(cd \"$OC\" && git remote -v 2>/dev/null | head -n 2) || true\n    if [[ -n \"$REMOTE_INFO\" ]]; then\n        echo \"$REMOTE_INFO\"\n        cd \"$OC\"\n        git add -A 2>/dev/null || true\n        CHANGES=$(git diff --cached --stat 2>/dev/null) || true\n        if [[ -n \"$CHANGES\" ]]; then\n            echo \"Changes:\"\n            echo \"$CHANGES\" | head -n 20\n            COMMIT_OUT=$(git commit -m \"nightly-audit: auto-backup $(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\" 2>&1) || true\n            echo \"$COMMIT_OUT\" | tail -n 3\n            PUSH_OUT=$(git push 2>&1) || true\n            if echo \"$PUSH_OUT\" | grep -qiE \"error|fatal|reject\"; then\n                echo \"⚠️ WARN: Git push failed\"\n                echo \"$PUSH_OUT\" | tail -n 5\n                inc_w\n            else\n                echo \"✅ Brain backup pushed successfully\"\n                inc_o\n            fi\n        else\n            echo \"✅ No changes to backup (repo is clean)\"\n            inc_o\n        fi\n    else\n        echo \"⚠️ WARN: Git repo exists but no remote configured\"\n        inc_w\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"⚠️ Brain backup not configured (no git repo in $OC)\"\n    echo \"  (Optional — setup: cd $OC && git init && git remote add origin <url>)\"\n    inc_w\nfi\n\n# =============================================================\n# Summary\n# =============================================================\necho \"\"\necho \"=============================================\"\necho \"  Summary: $CRITICAL critical · $WARN warn · $OK_COUNT ok\"\necho \"  Report : $REPORT_FILE\"\necho \"=============================================\"\n\n# --- Report rotation: keep last 30 days ---\nfind \"$REPORT_DIR\" -name \"audit-*.txt\" -mtime +30 -delete 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# Wait for tee process to finish writing\nsleep 1\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"opencode","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":6764,"cacheRead":38524,"cacheWrite":10260,"totalTokens":55549,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.1691,"cacheRead":0.019261999999999998,"cacheWrite":0.064125,"total":0.252492}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775115807685,"responseId":"msg_bdrk_01SPFoFjJcZ19Q6qppY4fNX4"}}
