{"type":"message","id":"35ec821e","parentId":"152f7824","timestamp":"2026-04-02T08:17:25.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bash path is correct `/usr/bin/bash`. But the exec-approvals change might not have been picked up by the gateway. Maybe I need to restart the gateway, or maybe the issue is that the cron session doesn't load the exec-approvals properly.\n\nActually, looking at the docs more carefully: \"Exec approvals are enforced locally on the execution host\" and the config is read from `~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json`. But the `askFallback: \"allowlist\"` should mean that when there's no UI to prompt (cron session), it falls back to the allowlist.\n\nWait - the cron session IS connected to the gateway, and the gateway CAN prompt. \n\nSo the real issue is that when the cron agent tries to execute something, the gateway sends an approval request, but there's no operator watching that specific session to approve it—even though the webchat UI is available elsewhere. The `askFallback` only kicks in when the UI is completely unreachable, not when it's just not monitoring that particular session. Maybe I should try setting the security level to \"full\" for the cron agent instead, or restart the gateway to ensure the config changes take effect. resolved by the ask fallback (default: deny).\"\n\nThe cron isolated session - does it have a UI? The web chat UI is connected to the main session. The cron session is isolated. So maybe there IS no UI for the cron session, and the askFallback should apply.\n\nBut it's still asking for approval... Maybe the gateway needs to be restarted to pick up the new exec-approvals.json? Or maybe the file format isn't quite right.\n\nLet me try a simpler approach - set `defaults.security` to `\"full\"` and `defaults.askFallback` to `\"full\"`. Actually no, that would bypass all approvals for everything.\n\nThe cleanest approach might be to restart the gateway to reload the config. Let me try that.\n\nActually wait - I just realized the exec-approvals.json might need a gateway restart to take effect since it's loaded at startup. Let me restart the gateway and see if that picks up the changes.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"可能需要重启 Gateway 让 exec-approvals 配置生效："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_013DTeAa6vELiGqnMesyy11T","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway restart"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"opencode","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":608,"cacheRead":108704,"cacheWrite":170,"totalTokens":109485,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.0152,"cacheRead":0.054352,"cacheWrite":0.0010625,"total":0.07062949999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775117823786,"responseId":"msg_bdrk_01U636q8HGwHaD6i1s3eEyvH"}}
