{"type":"message","id":"22ecaa0b","parentId":"ca7ff0df","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:25:37.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron run still shows the same issue - the isolated session agent is still asking for exec approval (`/approve d4b627f4 allow-once`). Even after the gateway restart and the exec-approvals.json change, it's still not working.\n\nThe issue might be that the allowlist patterns need to match differently. Looking at the exec-approvals docs more carefully:\n\n\"Patterns should resolve to binary paths (basename-only entries are ignored).\"\n\nMy patterns like `/usr/bin/bash` should be correct. But the cron session's agent is trying to run `bash /path/to/script.sh` - and the approval check might be checking the full command differently.\n\nActually wait - the user said they approved with \"ALWAYS APPROVED\" (allow-always). That should add the command to the allowlist automatically. But the cron run that just completed was BEFORE the user's always-approve action (since it was already running).\n\nThe user's \"always approved\" likely applies to their main session's exec commands, not the cron isolated session. The cron session has its own context.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The problem is the isolated cron session's agent is asking for approval, but nobody is there to approve. The `exec-approvals.json` config should handle this with `askFallback: \"allowlist\"`.\n\nLet me check what the current exec-approvals.json looks like after the user's allow-always actions may have modified it.\n\nActually, let me just try running the cron one more time - the user said they always-approved, maybe the next run will work. Or maybe I need to look at this from a different angle.\n\nActually, looking at the summary more carefully: \"需要你授权运行审计脚本\" - this is the LLM in the cron session saying it needs approval. The issue is that the exec tool in the isolated session is still requiring approval.\n\nThe `allow-always` the user clicked was for MY commands in the main session, not for the cron session's commands.\n\nFor the cron isolated session, the exec approval needs to be configured differently. Looking at the docs: `askFallback` determines what happens when no UI is available. But maybe the gateway considers the web UI as \"available\" even for the cron session, so it tries to prompt there, but the cron session isn't connected to the webchat UI.\n\nOr perhaps the approach should be to set `security: \"full\"` for the agent that runs cron jobs. But the cron uses the same `main` agent.\n\nActually, let me re-read the exec-approvals.json I configured:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"defaults\": {\n    \"security\": \"allowlist\",\n    \"ask\": \"on-miss\",\n    \"askFallback\": \"allowlist\"\n  },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"main\": {\n      \"security\": \"allowlist\",\n      \"ask\": \"on-miss\",\n      \"askFallback\": \"allowlist\",\n      \"allowlist\": [\n        {\"pattern\": \"/usr/bin/bash\"},\n        ...\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `askFallback: \"allowlist\"` should work when no UI is available. But maybe the issue is that the gateway restart didn't properly reload this file, or the user's allow-always actions overwrote my changes.\n\nLet me just check the current state of exec-approvals.json.\n\nActually, the user is getting very impatient. Let me be honest about the situation and suggest a simple workaround. The simplest approach that will definitely work: set `defaults.security: \"full\"` or `defaults.askFallback: \"full\"` for the cron case. Or alternatively, I can just tell the user to run the cron command themselves in terminal to verify it works.\n\nActually, let me think about this more practically. The user wants to go home. Let me:\n1. Check the current exec-approvals.json to see if it was overwritten\n2. If needed, set a more permissive fallback\n3. Do one final test\n\nOr better - let me just be upfront with the user about the remaining issue and give them a clear path to fix it."},{"type":"text","text":"还是卡在同一个问题上 — cron 的 isolated session 里 exec 审批无人响应。你刚才的 \"always approve\" 只对我们这个主会话生效，cron session 是隔离的。\n\n让我检查下配置文件现在的状态："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01Y3ufsNDeN8ko3LSUGR6eFo","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/gaoweiwei/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"opencode","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":1115,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":118740,"totalTokens":119858,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.027875,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.742125,"total":0.770015}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775129108693,"responseId":"msg_01SFfPQo49Y9kvAb3LzCtBdU"}}
